Description: Holy Family; the Virgin seated on a rock to right, holding the Christ Child on her knee; with St Joseph standing by a tree behind to left, holding a staff. Woodcut
Curator's comments: Originally attributed to Nuvolone by Weigel, as cited by Nagler; taken to be his only print, and in the manner of Guido Reni.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Mrs H P Hacker
